description: Welcome to the Sabine Valley Amateur Radio Association (SVARA). We are located in Greenville – Hunt County, Texas, approximately 40 miles east of the Dallas/Ft. Worth metro area.  We are a group of Amateur Radio operators with a friendly focus on the education and public service components of the HAM radio hobby. We are the *SkyWarn* organization for Hunt County, assisting the National Weather Service whenever sever weather threatens.  SVARA was established in Hunt County over 50 years ago and has been active since that time. The club almost disappeared in 2004 as the membership & support of club activities diminished, but with the foresight of a few SVARA members the club has made a turnaround. The SVARA officers and members are committed to placing SVARA back in the mainstream of community activities and public support that it once had. Thanks for visiting our website and we hope to hear from you.  The Sabine Valley Amateur Radio Association operates and maintains multiple repeater

description: ----------------- Group Description -----------------  ** At registration, please be sure to *include your CALLSIGN and indicate if you are a current member of WSARC.*  The West Seattle Amateur Radio Club is your best-bet for social contact or technical assistance from the local hams in West Seattle. The club has a rich history stretching back to the 1930's. We offer weekly radio nets on three club repeaters using the club call of W7AW and monthly breakfasts and club meetings in West Seattle.  We host a monthly club meeting on the third Saturday of each month, from 9:30-11:00ish at the Salvation Army Community Center, in White Center. And, a monthly Elmers' Breakfast Gathering & Help Session, every 1st Saturday from 8:00-9:30 am, at the Great American Diner & Bar.  The club offers licensing classes to become a ham radio operator. Classes and exams are available for anyone interested in joining our community. If you live or operate in the West Seattle area, or can get to West Seattle
